            <h3>Lucena City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Try the City’s native products like the tinapa (smoked fish) and chami (a locally manufactured noodle).</li>
                <li>2. Visit Lucena’s Fish Port in Barangay Dalahican and pick the freshest seafoods.</li>
                <li>3. Visit Lucena’s historical landmarks like Manuel L. Quezon Heritage Site, Perez Park, St. Ferdinand Cathedral, Quezon Provincial Capitol Building, and the Lucena City Hall (Main Building).</li>
                <li>4. Eat in the City’s best restaurants like Queen Margarette Court (Diversion Road, Brgy. Domoit); Grand Riviera Hotel (Diversion Road, Brgy. Ilayang Dupay); South Waters Marina and Country Club (Brgy. Ibabang Iyam); Ouans Worth Farm (Diversion Road, Brgy. Kanlurang Mayao); Lucena Fresh Air Hotel (Maharlika H-way, Brgy. Isabang); Restorante de Lucena (Quezon Avenue); Hacienda Inn (Quezon Avenue); Mug Café (Pacific Mall; JM Premiere Cuisine (Quezon Avenue); Buddy Pizza (Quezon Avenue); Plaza Food House (Profugo St.); and Koffee Klatch (Quezon Avenue)</li>
                <li>5. Buy the latest souvenirs in La Moda Filipina (cor. Enverga and Merchan Sts.); Lucena Public Market. For sweets and pasalubong: Villamater (Quezon Avenue); Galeon Sweets and Pasalubong (Quezon Avenue); and Koffee Klatch (Quezon Avenue).</li>
            </ol>

